Lara Jones was a series of explicit erotic color comic books written and drawn by writer-artist Paco Diaz (born Luque Francisco Diaz, 1967; worked with Marvel Comics in several titles), from 2000 to 2003 for Eros Comix, the adult-oriented imprint of Dolmen Publishing (Spain), in Spanish. As far as I know there is no actual published comic book title for Lara Jones, only excerpts from Eros Comix. Such is the case with the five comic books posted here: the first, "Lara Jones and The Amazons", is feature-length and complete, depicting the origins of the title character, obviously a blonde, uninhibited hybrid of the fictional Indiana Jones and Lara Croft, in comic book format (CBZ); and the rest a compilation of the stories "Stressful Day", "Treasure of Osiris", "The Hammer of Thor" and "The Final Penetration," all were translated from the original Spanish by a certain Regdul14 and then scanned by a certain Halibut72. Suffice it to say that certainly because of the author-artist, the plots are surprisingly above average for the genre with great and distinctive artwork. Even so, graphic and explicit. For Mature readers only.
